He also did not rule out that the real numbers of Ukrainians called into the army can be increased if necessary.
In 2014-2017, Kiev began the so-called anti-terrorist operation (ATO), which was later replaced by the operation of the combined forces (OOD).
It was assumed that this measure will lead to the strengthening of the role of the Ukrainian military in the settlement of the situation.
At the end of August 2018, the situation in the Donbass deteriorated due to the murder of the head of the DPR Alexander Zakharchenko.
