According to CNBC TV channel, the pre-trial arrangement with the Department allows Mask to remain on a senior post in Tesla.
At the same time, he is obliged to pay $20 million and to leave the post of Chairman of the Board of Directors within 45 days from the date of the agreement and for at least three years.
Two independent directors will be appointed to his seats. $
It is specified that the agreement still has to be approved by the court.
On September 28, it became known that the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission accused Mask of misleading shareholders with a statement that sufficient funds were available for redemption of shares of this company and filed on the entrepreneur in court.
It is about the publication of the businessman on Twitter, where he declared desire to redeem shares of Tesla at $420 per piece, but didn't do it.
After the tweet, the company's shares rose by almost 11%.
The head of the British Foreign Ministry compared the EU with the Soviet Union and prison
British Foreign Minister Jeremy Hunt compared the European Union with the Soviet Union and accused Brussels of captivity of member countries of the community.
The diplomat made such a statement at the Congress of the ruling Conservative Party in Birmingham, which opened on Sunday, September 30.
According to the Daily Mail, thus Hunt commented on the difficulties in the negotiation process on Brexit.
What happened to the belief in the European dream and its ideals?
The EU was created to protect freedom, and the Soviet Union did not let anyone leave it.
The lesson of history is obvious: if you turn the EU from community to prison, the desire to leave it will not diminish, but will only grow, and we will not be the only prisoner who wants to escape from captivity,” said the minister.
He also added that attempts to punish Britain for the decision to leave the European Union will only aggravate the crisis, notes “Gazeta.ru”.
In mid-September, British Prime Minister Theresa May said that negotiations on Brexit have come to an impasse.
So she commented on the results of the informal summit of the European Union in Salzburg.
The decision on Brexit was made in 2016 following the results of a referendum.
It is expected that the withdrawal of the United Kingdom should take place before April 2019, but negotiations with Brussels on this issue are complicated by many factors.
In particular, there is still no clear agreement on how the parties will interact after London leaves the community.
In addition, the question of the Irish border remains open.
