Elon Musk forced to leave the post of head of the board of directors of Tesla
The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission and Tesla founder Elon Musk settled their dispute in the case of fraud.
This is reported by CNBC News.
According to the TV channel, within the framework of the agreements, Mask will have to leave the post of head of the Board of Directors of Tesla.
At the same time, the commission allowed Mask to keep the post of head Tesla.
As noted, the founder of Tesla will also have to pay an administrative fine of $20 million.
The same amount will be collected from Tesla.
At the same time money will be distributed among the affected investors.
In addition, the company must appoint two independent directors.
Elon Musk - an American entrepreneur, included in the list of 50 richest people on the planet according to Forbes magazine.
He is the head of SpaceX Space Corporation, Neuralink Neuralink and Tesla electric car developer, and co-founder of Paypal.
The US Securities and Exchange Commission has previously sued Tesla CEO Ilon Musk because of his Twitter announcement about a possible redemption of the company.
Last month Musk announced plans to make Tesla a private company and buy back all shares on the stock exchange at a fixed price of $420.
The cost of the share in $420 was established allegedly “because of the importance of this number in the culture of marijuana”, reported earlier Bloomberg with reference to the co-director of the security department of the Commission Stephen Paykin.
At the same time, Elon Musk subsequently refused his plans to redeem the shares.
Commenting on the lawsuit filed against him by the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, the businessman said that he considers the fraud charges unfounded, and added that he is very disappointed and saddened by these claims. $
“Honesty is the most important value of my life, and the facts will prove that I have not broken it in any way,” the businessman said in an interview with CNBC.
At the same time in August, the group of shareholders Tesla filed against Mask a collective action, complaining about the financial losses suffered.
The plaintiffs claimed that the businessman's posts caused them losses.
In particular, one of the shareholders said that tweets of the businessman were misleading, because of which sellers of Tesla shares were forced to buy papers at artificially inflated prices to cover their positions.
Also other plaintiffs noted that careless statements of Ilon Mask led to sharp fluctuations of the course.
In September, Ilona Muska accused of exchange fraud and the head of the research company Citron Research.
Meanwhile, if Musk could not settle his dispute with the US Securities and Exchange Commission, he would be threatened with suspension from the management of the company and even prison.
This, in particular, declared to CNBC TV channel former chairman of the commission Harvey Pitt.
Musk - “a good guy who does not know how to run a car company.”
