More than 100 prisoners escaped from prison in Indonesia after earthquake
More than 100 prisoners escaped from prison in Central Sulawesi province of Indonesia.
The escape was possible after two powerful earthquakes on the island of magnitude 7.2 and 7.4.
According to The Jakarta Post, the incident took place on September 28, when prisoners in Palu prison demanded their release due to the tremors.
More than 340 prisoners staged a riot and set fire to the facility.
The police officers who have arrived to the place of state of emergency partially took a situation under control, but more than 100 people have escaped from prison.
The building itself has been seriously damaged, and guards have difficulty in holding prisoners.
The number of victims of the earthquake and tsunami that occurred on Sulawesi Island increased to 832.
As a result, it is still not possible to establish transport, electricity and communications with parts of the island. $
“Golden Pearl” for “extreme realism”
The San Sebastian International Film Festival recognized the Spanish film for the third time in history as the best film of the year.
The main award - “Golden Sink” - was awarded to the drama “The Two Seas” directed by Isaki Lacuesta.
