The names of the winners of the Fazil Iskander Prize became known
Awards were given to the winners of the Fazil Iskander Prize.
The ceremony was held at the Central House of Writers in Moscow.
In the nomination “Prose” the winner was Kanta Ibragimov, novel “Stigal”.
The novel “Stigal” begins as a diary of a cancer patient and turns to the final into an epic work.
In the nomination “Poetry” - Vyacheslav Shapovalov, book of poems “Euroazis”.
“The best screenplay” - the work of Sergey Dmitrenko based on the stories told by Fazil Iskander in the book “Sandro from Chegem”.
In the nomination “Chegemsky heights” - Auren Habichev, a series of stories “My Great Nothing”.
In addition to the main competition special diplomas were awarded to Elena Nesterina for the novel “Eternal happiness!” and Lyudmila Vyazmitinova for the book of poems “Months”, reports TASS.
Fazil Iskander (1929 - 2016) was born in Sukhumi.
In 1954 he graduated from the Literary Institute.
The first poetic collections - “Mountain trails” (1957), “Kindness of the earth” (1959), “Green rain” (1960) - were recognized by critics and readers.
Real fame brought him the story “Constellation of Kozlotur” (1966).
The most famous novel by Iskander - “Sandro of Chegem”.
