“The arrival of such technologies is a unique thing, it is a huge benefit.
This is the explosive growth of medical technologies, it is the improvement of quality of life and infrastructure.
But there is a second side.
The development of nature-like technologies is actually a technological reproduction of wildlife systems.
There is a reverse side - purposeful intervention in human life.
There are always risks.
There was a car - people began to perish under wheels.
But cars still use.
The dual nature of technology at once.
I create medical new technology, and at the same time I can create weapons of mass destruction ", - quotes the scientist REN TV.
