Every resident of Kalmykia is a debtor
Residents of the republic increasingly visit the official website of the Office of the Federal Bailiff Service of Russia in the Republic of Kazakhstan.
According to the specialists of the department of organizational-control work, informatization and information security of the republican department, over the past eight months more than 140 have been registered thousand visits to the site itself, more than 42 thousand - section “Data bank of enforcement proceedings”, 661 payment receipt on payment of debts are downloaded.
According to Valery Bogdanov, Chairman of the Public Council at the UFSSP of Russia in the Republic of Kazakhstan, almost every resident of the region has debts for utilities, fines of traffic police, bank loans, loans, $ and no one is immune from unforeseen situations. $
But debtors may have negative consequences in the form of, for example, a ban on travel abroad.
That is why UFSSP of Russia in the Republic of Kazakhstan recommends to all who have planned a trip abroad, to clarify in the department of bailiffs at the place of residence or on the site www.r08fssprus.ru information about the presence of unpaid debts and pay them off. $
The service has created a “Data Bank of Enforcement Proceedings” for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is available not only on the regional websites of UFSSP Russia, but also on social networks and mobile communication devices iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The data bank contains information on enforcement proceedings initiated by Kalmyk bailiffs against all debtors, - explains Delgir Bodgaeva, assistant head of UFSSP Russia for Kazakhstan.
“If there are debts, the system displays information about the number and date of initiation of enforcement proceedings; the name of the body that issued the executive sheet or other act; its number, amount and type debt; address of the department of bailiffs; full name of the bailiff; contact phone.
Information on the progress of enforcement proceedings can also be obtained on the portal of public services at: http://epgu.gosuslugi.ru”
